regrettable.<br/> Muazu Ibrahim</p><p>An overbearing governor<br/> Yakubu Aruwa<br/> We don’t like the truth, so we often misinterpret it in Nigeria. Using public properties for compensation of allies is a crime against the public. It should be recovered<br/> David Adejo</p><div style="clear:both; margin-top:0em; margin-bottom:1em;"><a href="https://www.peoplesdailyng.com/aftermath-of-former-chief-of-army-staff-others-tragic-death/" target="_blank" rel="dofollow" class="ubea41e901ecd8c9f48251991d61ff0d9"><style> .ubea41e901ecd8c9f48251991d61ff0d9 { padding:0px; margin: 0; padding-top:1em!important; padding-bottom:1em!important; width:100%; display: block; font-weight:bold; background-color:#eaeaea; border:0!important; border-left:4px solid #34495E!important; text-decoration:none; } .ubea41e901ecd8c9f48251991d61ff0d9:active, .ubea41e901ecd8c9f48251991d61ff0d9:hover { opacity: 1; transition: opacity 250ms; webkit-transition: opacity 250ms; text-decoration:none; } .ubea41e901ecd8c9f48251991d61ff0d9 { transition: background-color 250ms; webkit-transition: background-color 250ms; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 250ms; webkit-transition: opacity 250ms; } .ubea41e901ecd8c9f48251991d61ff0d9 .ctaText { font-weight:bold; color:#464646; text-decoration:none; font-size: 16px; } .ubea41e901ecd8c9f48251991d61ff0d9 .postTitle { color:#000000; text-decoration: underline!important; font-size: 16px; } .ubea41e901ecd8c9f48251991d61ff0d9:hover .postTitle { text-decoration: underline!important; } </style><div style="padding-left:1em; padding-right:1em;"><span class="ctaText">READ MORE</span>&nbsp; <span class="postTitle">Aftermath of former chief of army staff, others’ tragic death</span></div></a></div><p>He should turn the hotel building to school instead of demolition, if not bad intentions and a planned act of vendetta<br/> Hamisu Abdullahi</p><p>There is really no sense in the demolition of the already completed structure which was built with public funds. Even if the erstwhile governor had appropriated it to himself or crony it would have been better to take it back and put it into public use.<br/> Ginger</p><p>The new Governor needed to follow the due process of serving the requisite notices on the ‘’owners’’ and not embarked on nocturnal and clandestine destruction of such properties.<br/> MystaMan</p><p>Today is for you and tomorrow is for someone else.<br/> Haruna Gabo</p><p>I am not against recovering of government’s property. What I’m against is the destruction of valuable properties instead of putting them into a proper use.<br/> Mancele</p><p>Today is for you and tomorrow is for someone else.<br/> Haruna Gabo</p><div style="clear:both; margin-top:0em; margin-bottom:1em;"><a href="https://www.peoplesdailyng.com/post-covid-19-the-future-of-nigeria-economy/" target="_blank" rel="dofollow" class="u6e6cc1664f10681c42e9ab41be96270d"><style> .u6e6cc1664f10681c42e9ab41be96270d { padding:0px; margin: 0; padding-top:1em!important; padding-bottom:1em!important; width:100%; display: block; font-weight:bold; background-color:#eaeaea; border:0!important; border-left:4px solid #34495E!important; text-decoration:none; } .u6e6cc1664f10681c42e9ab41be96270d:active, .u6e6cc1664f10681c42e9ab41be96270d:hover { opacity: 1; transition: opacity 250ms; webkit-transition: opacity 250ms; text-decoration:none; } .u6e6cc1664f10681c42e9ab41be96270d { transition: background-color 250ms; webkit-transition: background-color 250ms; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 250ms; webkit-transition: opacity 250ms; } .u6e6cc1664f10681c42e9ab41be96270d .ctaText { font-weight:bold; color:#464646; text-decoration:none; font-size: 16px; } .u6e6cc1664f10681c42e9ab41be96270d .postTitle { color:#000000; text-decoration: underline!important; font-size: 16px; } .u6e6cc1664f10681c42e9ab41be96270d:hover .postTitle { text-decoration: underline!important; } </style><div style="padding-left:1em; padding-right:1em;"><span class="ctaText">READ MORE</span>&nbsp; <span class="postTitle">Post-COVID-19: The future of Nigeria economy</span></div></a></div><p>Kwankwaso cannot be seen as ‘’the emerging strongman of Northern Nigeria politics’’, not with just one state in the North. And the new governor is laying a bad foundation for destruction and counter destructions because he is only going to be there for four years, at most eight years<br/> Black Man</p><p>Abba is just dancing to the tune of Kwankwaso because of his loyalty to him. Kwankwaso is observing his third term in disguise.<br/> Anonymous</p><p>Ganduje should be blamed for all that is happening in Kano state. Kwanwasao broke the record of using his deputy to succeed him, only for Ganduje to bite the finger that brought him to power,<br/> Anonymous</p><p>It is important for our politicians to always remember that power is transient and there should be a time limit within the life of an administration beyond which they are not permitted to make new appointments, employments or sign contracts on behalf of the Government<br/> Obekezie Frank</p><div style="clear:both; margin-top:0em; margin-bottom:1em;"><a href="https://www.peoplesdailyng.com/the-mad-rush-for-revenues/" target="_blank" rel="dofollow" class="u522768497ffd7d4f942e80aa812e6455"><style> .u522768497ffd7d4f942e80aa812e6455 { padding:0px; margin: 0; padding-top:1em!important; padding-bottom:1em!important; width:100%; display: block; font-weight:bold; background-color:#eaeaea; border:0!important; border-left:4px solid #34495E!important; text-decoration:none; } .u522768497ffd7d4f942e80aa812e6455:active, .u522768497ffd7d4f942e80aa812e6455:hover { opacity: 1; transition: opacity 250ms; webkit-transition: opacity 250ms; text-decoration:none; } .u522768497ffd7d4f942e80aa812e6455 { transition: background-color 250ms; webkit-transition: background-color 250ms; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 250ms; webkit-transition: opacity 250ms; } .u522768497ffd7d4f942e80aa812e6455 .ctaText { font-weight:bold; color:#464646; text-decoration:none; font-size: 16px; } .u522768497ffd7d4f942e80aa812e6455 .postTitle { color:#000000; text-decoration: underline!important; font-size: 16px; } .u522768497ffd7d4f942e80aa812e6455:hover .postTitle { text-decoration: underline!important; } </style><div style="padding-left:1em; padding-right:1em;"><span class="ctaText">READ MORE</span>&nbsp; <span class="postTitle">The mad rush for revenues</span></div></a></div><p>An agreement was signed with developers that is binding on Kano state government whether he likes it or not and he will pay compensation to the company adequately. That is a waste of scarce resources of the state.<br/> Wondergate</p><p>It is not vengeance; it is recovering public properties illegally sold to wife, biological son and daughters, political party members and friends. The five star hotel was built over the functional institute for Hospitality and Tourism belonging to the University of Science and Technology, Wudil. The masses of Kano state need more schools not luxury hotels.<br/> Basiru Yakasai</p><p>Madam, your write up on Kano was very good and well researched. Please note that Kwankwaso was not the first governor to have handed over to his deputy after his tenure ended. Former Zamfara Governor, Sani Yerima handed over to his then deputy, Shinkafa in 2003<br/> Mustapha Shehu</p><p>I just finished reading your article on Abba. I have a reservation you are not being optimistic 08107921993</p></div><p><script data-cfasync="false" src="/cdn-cgi/scripts/5c5dd728/cloudflare-static/email-decode.min.js"></script><script async src="https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script> <ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display: block; text-align: center;" data-ad-layout="in-article" data-ad-format="fluid" data-ad-client="ca-pub-3496627917102011" data-ad-slot="1728586239"></ins> <script> (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({}); </script></p></div></div><div class="post-author"> <a href="https://www.peoplesdailyng.com/author/naroto/" class="avatar-link"